It took me a little while to write this one… because this closing means so much to me 🥹❤️

My amazing friend Guadalupe and her husband Juan just closed on their very first home and I had the honor of being their Realtor.

I met Guadalupe three years ago while I was out at Lions Park selling juices. Yup, I used to hustle hard out there with my cooler and juices, rain or shine! 🍋💪🏽 Never would’ve thought that small encounter would turn into something so special years later.

What makes this even more special is that they finally took that leap choosing to buy a home instead of continuing to rent. That decision takes courage, vision, and faith… and I couldn’t be happier for them 🙏🏽

We got their closing costs paid, the fridge included, and they’re already walking in with equity! They closed on a lovely home in Nolanville, in a neighborhood they can truly grow into and be proud of.

Grateful. Proud. Full circle moment. Congratulations Guadalupe & Juan 💕🏡
